cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a method that incorporates reliability information and uses optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the use of kurtosis-based updating, which is a statistical measure, indicating that cs.ST (Statistics Theory) could also be a possible category. The proposed method involves modeling the state of the tracker, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on video datasets, which is related to multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
